Volcano Ash Chile Volcano Prompts Flight Delays in Argentina

-- B y   E l i a n a   R a s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-06-25T13:28:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/volcano-ash-chile-volcano-prompts-flight-delays-in-argentina.html
Some flights to and from  Argentina 
were canceled or delayed today because of an ash cloud from a
volcanic eruption in Chile, according to information posted on
the airports operator.  AMR Corp. (AMR)  American Airlines’ flights from Miami, New York
and Dallas that were scheduled to arrive this morning at Buenos
Aires international airport were canceled, according to
Aeropuertos Argentina 2000 SA’s  website . Arrivals from Lima, Rio
de Janeiro and Miami by Aerolineas Argentinas SA were canceled
while departures to Madrid and Rome were delayed.  Lan Airlines SA, Latin America’s biggest airline by market
value, yesterday canceled all flights to and from Buenos Aires
and said it may resume flights sometime today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Eliana Raszewski in  Buenos Aires  at 
 eraszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  